			<div class="content" id="post-content-2739967">
									

<p>For the hard sci-fi lovers among us (I know you guys are here), the <a href="http://www.projectrho.com/public_html/rocket/">Atomic Rockets</a> website is a fantastic resource for space and sci-fi realism. It mainly focuses on rocketry, but it also has a lot of other info that may be useful. Another good one is the <a href="http://toughsf.blogspot.com/">Tough SF</a> blog, which has some useful info. If you guys have any other useful websites of a similar nature, respond to this with links to them!</p>
<p>Also, while it is primarily math focused, <a href="https://www.khanacademy.org/">Khan Academy</a> does have some great resources on other subjects as well, including physics, history, and astronomy.</p>

							</div>

								
