			<div class="content" id="post-content-2768051">
									

<p>While it might be more of a guide, <a href="http://www.ohsu.edu/xd/education/schools/school-of-medicine/departments/clinical-departments/psychiatry/education-and-training/medical-students/upload/MSE-Psychiatric-Interviewing.pdf">Interviewing Psychiatric Patients (John Morrison, M. D.)</a> details the different methods and techniques used when interviewing psychiatric patients. In addition, it describes different mental disorders and the way patients with those disorders act and speak during interviews, going into great depth and giving examples of such behavior. It might be helpful if anyone is struggling with creating a realistic interview in their writing.</p>

